Bootstraps a project scaffolded from `template/` by building the `ctx-*` tool binaries from a separate CTX tooling repo and copying them plus their prompt files into the local project — since the tools themselves live outside this template and aren't part of the project's own crates.

Takes the CTX repo path as `$1`, falling back to `$CTX_REPO` env var, then `../CTX`; fails fast if `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` isn't found there. Builds packages `(ctx-context ctx-scan ctx-verify ctx-cage ctx-summarize ctx-brief)` via one `cargo build -p ...` invocation in the CTX repo, then copies binaries into `target/debug/` — note `BINARIES` has seven entries, not six, because `ctx-cage`'s package produces two binaries (`ctx-cage` and `ctx-run`); keep these two arrays in sync manually if the tooling repo adds/renames packages or binaries.

Also copies `summarizer-leaf.md` and `summarizer-rollup.md` from the CTX repo's `prompts/` into local `./prompts/`, since `ctx-scan`/`ctx-summarize` resolve that path relative to cwd (the project root) at runtime, not relative to the tooling repo. Intended to be re-run any time the tooling repo updates or immediately after copying `template/` into a new project — it always overwrites existing binaries/prompts, no version check.